# Integration Test Report — Player 10001 (Batch-Only Scenario)

## Correlation Map

| Source Module | Trigger | Target Module(s) | Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|
| **SignIn** → checkin | Day claimed | **Mail** | Auto-sends a mail with the sign-in reward as an attachment (e.g., `[Mail] sent: Sign-in Day 1 Reward (id=1)`) |
| **SignIn** → claimreward | Reward claimed | **SignIn** (self) | Prints `reward claimed again` — always succeeds even if already claimed (no dedup guard) |
| **Bag** → additem | Item added | **Task** | Adding an item increments task progress (task 3001 "obtain item" completed after first `additem`) |
| **Task** → completion | Task finished | **Achievement** | Completing a task triggers achievement unlock (task 3001 → achievement 4001 `first_task`) |
| **Task** → completion | Task finished | **Mail** | Completing a task sends achievement notification mail (e.g., `[Mail] sent: Achievement Unlocked! (id=4001) (id=2)`) |
| **Bag** → additem | 100 items added | **Achievement** | Adding 100 of one item unlocks achievement 4003 `collector_100` |
| **Equipment** → equip | Both slots filled | **Achievement** | Having both weapon and armor equipped unlocks achievement 4004 `fully_equipped` |
| **Equipment** → equip | Item equipped | **Equipment** (self) | Equipping into an occupied slot silently overwrites (auto-equip replaces previous) |
| **Achievement** → unlock | Achievement unlocked | **Mail** | Achievement unlock auto-sends notification mail, but some have no attachment (achievement mails 4001, 4004, 4003 had no claimable attachment) |
| **Mail** → claimmail | Mail claimed | **Bag** | Claiming a mail attachment adds the item to bag (e.g., `item 2001 x1` from mail 1) |

## Defect Report

| # | Severity | Module(s) | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| **D1** | 🔴 **High** | SignIn / ClaimReward | **ClaimReward has no duplicate-check.** Calling `claimreward` for a day that was already claimed logs `"day N reward claimed again"` with no error — it always succeeds. This means a player can infinitely claim sign-in rewards by repeatedly calling `claimreward` for the same day. The `checkin` command correctly blocks re-claims (`"day 1 already claimed"`), but `claimreward` does not. |
| **D2** | 🟠 **Medium** | SignIn | **Day sequence is not enforced.** Player can check in for day 5 without having checked in for day 4. Day 4 can be retroactively claimed later. There is no sequential gating. |
| **D3** | 🟠 **Medium** | Equipment | **Equipping a non-existent item succeeds.** Equipping `itemId=9999` (never added to bag) logs `auto-equip: weapon slot → item 9999` without error. The server does not validate that the item exists in the player's bag before equipping. |
| **D4** | 🟠 **Medium** | Equipment | **Equipping into an occupied slot silently overwrites.** When equipping item 2001 into the weapon slot that already held item 2001 (or another item), the previous item is silently replaced with no unequip event, no return-to-bag log, and no warning. |
| **D5** | 🟡 **Low** | Equipment / Items | **Same item can be equipped in multiple slots simultaneously.** Item 2001 was auto-equipped into both `weapon` and `armor` slots at the same time (`Batch #3` logs). There is no exclusivity check preventing the same item instance from occupying two slots. |
| **D6** | 🟡 **Low** | Achievement / Mail | **Achievement notification mails have no attachments (except they trigger task chains).** Mails for achievements 4001, 4003, 4004 were sent with `claim failed: mail has no attachment`. This may be intentional (notification-only), but the design is inconsistent — some mails have attachments (sign-in rewards) and some don't, with no visual distinction. |
| **D7** | 🟡 **Low** | Task | **Task 3002 (target 2) never completed despite completing day 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5.** Task 3002 was initialized at batch start with `target 2`, but even after 5 sign-ins it never triggered a progress update or completion. The sign-in module does not appear to feed into task 3002's progress counter, suggesting a broken or unlinked task trigger. |

## Confidence Assessment

| Finding | Confidence | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| D1 – ClaimReward duplicate | **95%** | Reproduced consistently across Batches 1, 2, 3, 5, 6. Contrast with checkin's correct `"already claimed"` guard is clear evidence. |
| D2 – Day sequence not enforced | **90%** | Day 5 claimed before day 4, then day 4 retroactively succeeded. Clear ordering violation. |
| D3 – Equip non-existent item | **95%** | itemId=9999 was never added but equipping it succeeded with no error in Batch 6. |
| D4 – Silent slot overwrite | **85%** | Observed in multiple batches. No unequip or return-to-bag event logged on overwrite. |
| D5 – Same item dual-slot | **85%** | Item 2001 appeared in both weapon and armor simultaneously (Batch 3). Could be intentional if items are "types" not "instances", but still likely a bug. |
| D6 – Achievement mails no attachment | **80%** | Consistently observed. May be by design, but worth flagging as inconsistent UX. |
| D7 – Task 3002 never progresses | **90%** | Task 3002 was created with target 2 at init. Five sign-ins and multiple item operations never triggered it. Task 3001 (target 1) completed on first additem, confirming the task system works for some triggers but not 3002. |
| **Correlation Map** | **90-95%** | All cross-module chains were observed directly in batch logs across 6 batch executions. |
